AOE Link Handler

  Version
    * 1.1.0

  ERROR prompt:
    * Oops, an error occurred!
      Invalid form/module token detected. Access Denied!

  Context
    * If you are clicking on an item in the page tree of the link wizard

  Help by wiki.typo3.org
    * http://wiki.typo3.org/Exception/CMS/1392409507
    * In custom backend modules it is usually necessary to generate links to the module using BackendUtility::getModuleUrl() method
      http://typo3.org/api/typo3cms/class_t_y_p_o3_1_1_c_m_s_1_1_backend_1_1_utility_1_1_backend_utility.html#a8437ed5134d2c407ca67cc5f5627b280)
    * In the case of wizards the usage of the "script" key for type=>script wizards is deprecated.
      Instead the configuration option "module" should get used
      http://docs.typo3.org/typo3cms/TCAReference/AdditionalFeatures/WizardsConfiguration/Index.html#wizards-configuration-script-script

